# OpenE2EE — mobile/ios/Runner.xcodeproj — Xcode project internal ignores
# PR-25 (Sprint 4) — project.pbxproj is now COMMITTED.
#
# ─── STATUS (post-PR-25) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# `project.pbxproj` is hand-written and tracked. `xcuserdata/`,
# `xcuserstate`, and per-user scheme state MUST be ignored so opening
# the project in Xcode doesn't accidentally regenerate the file or
# drag per-machine state into git.
#
# ─── RATIONALE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Hand-writing the pbxproj is brittle — see `docs/ios/xcodeproj-structure.md`
# for the layout. We commit a hand-written scaffold because:
#
#   1. `flutter create` re-rolls UUIDs on every run, creating churn
#      across teammates' working trees.
#   2. The XcodeGen / Tuist route would add a non-trivial CI
#      dependency. PR-25 keeps the project file as-is and leaves
#      generator migration as Sprint 4+ follow-up.
#
# ─── IGNORES ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Per-user Xcode state — never commit.
/xcuserdata/
*.xcuserstate

# Workspace data that is regenerated by Xcode on every open.
/project.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/

# Per-user schemes (team-shared schemes go in xcshareddata/, which is
# committed once schemes are added in a Sprint 4 follow-up).
/xcuserdata/$(USER).xcuserdatad/xcschemes/*